#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1632
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Dealing with Enemies</title>"
msgstr "<title>Kako sa Neprijateljima</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can always trap a single oncoming enemy in one hole, get his gold and "
"run on over him without killing him. It is often a good idea to dig behind "
"you and delay him further, but that might kill him. In some levels it is not "
"a good idea to kill enemies."
msgstr ""
"Uvijek možete zarobiti jednog neprijatelja u rupu, uzeti mu zlato i "
"pretrčati ga bez da izgubite život, Dobra ideja je da se kopa iza sebe da bi "
"ga držali na distanci, ali to ga može ubiti što u nekim nivoima nije dobra "
"stvar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1642
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can usually trap two oncoming enemies in two holes, get their gold and "
"run on over them, but this is dangerous if the enemies are separated by two "
"or three spaces. Sometimes two holes kill one of the enemies and the other "
"escapes and sometimes both escape. In &kgoldrunner; rules it is easier to "
"trap two enemies and run over them, because they stay in the holes for "
"longer."
msgstr ""
"Obično možete zarobiti dva neprijatelja u dvije rupe, uzeti im zlato i "
"pretrčati ih, ali je ovo jako opasno ako su malo dalje jedan od drugog, "
"ponekad jedna rupa ubije neprijatelja a drugi pobjegne a ponekad obojca "
"pobjegnu. Prema &kgoldrunner; pravilima lakše je zarobiti dva neprijatelja i "
"pretrčati ih jer su u rupama duže."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is nearly always impossible to trap three oncoming enemies and run on "
"over them. You will have to kill them, dig and drop through the floor or "
"simply run away."
msgstr ""
"Gotovo je nemoguće zarobiti tri neprijatelja i pretrčati ih. Morat ćete ih "
"ubiti, iskopati im rupu bez dna ili jednostavno pobjeći."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1655
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Try to get all the enemies running together in one group. That way you will "
"not get surrounded and you can do such fun things as collect gold while they "
"run along behind you."
msgstr ""
"Pokušajte natjerati neprijatelje da se kreću u grupi. Tako se nećete naći u "
"situaciji da ste okruženi, a usput će vam biti lakše kupiti zlato dok vas "
"grupa proganja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1660
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sometimes you can kill an enemy with two holes, but it often takes three to "
"nine holes to kill one to five enemies."
msgstr ""
"Ponekad možete ubiti neprijatelja sa dvije rupe, ali potrebno je od 3 do 9 "
"rupa da ubijete od jednog do pet neprijatelja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to kill an enemy with one hole if he is far enough away when "
"you dig it."
msgstr ""
"Moguće je ubiti neprijatelja i sa samo jednom rupom ako je dovoljno daleko "
"od nje kada je iskopate."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <quote>Traditional</quote> game, you can trap an enemy permanently in "
"a pit of brick or concrete. Stand near the edge of the pit on the opposite "
"side to the enemy. As he approaches the pit, move down one square (to the "
"level of the floor of the pit) and the enemy will usually run into the pit."
msgstr ""
"U <quote>Standardno</quote>j igi , možete zarobiti neprijatelja zuvijek u "
"rupi od cigli ili betona. Stanine na rub rupe suprotno od neprijatelja. I "
"pomjerite se jedan kvadratić dole (na nivo dubine rupe) tako da neprijatelj "
"utrči u rupu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1675
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some levels in the <quote>Traditional</quote> game, you can force an "
"enemy to climb a ladder ahead of you if you stand somewhere above the bottom "
"of the ladder."
msgstr ""
"Na nekim nivoima <quote>Standardno</quote> igre, možete natjerati "
"neprijatelja da se popne uz merdevine ako stanete negdje iznad dna merdevina."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1680
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <quote>&kgoldrunner;</quote> game, you can trap an enemy in a pit by "
"getting him to fall from above you, then running sideways and digging out "
"before he reaches you."
msgstr ""
"U <quote>&kgoldrunner;</quote> igri, možete zarobiti neprijatelja u rupu ako "
"ga pustite da padne iznad vas, dok vi brzo iskopate rupu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <quote>&kgoldrunner;</quote> game, enemies cannot run through dug "
"bricks, so you can sometimes use them as a barrier or hiding place."
msgstr ""
"U <quote>&kgoldrunner;</quote> igri, neprijatelji ne mogu trčati kroz "
"iskopane cigle, pa ih možete koristiti kao barijeru ili mjesto za skrivanje."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1693
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Digging Puzzles</title>"
msgstr "<title>Mozgalice kopanja</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1697
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To dig through more than one layer of bricks, start by digging as many "
"bricks as there are layers, jump in, dig one brick less and so on."
msgstr ""
"Da iskopate više od jednog sloja cigli, počnite sa kopanjem onliko cigli "
"koliko vam treba slojeva,uskoči, iskopaj jednu rupu manje nego prije, i tako "
"dalje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1702
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you dig next to a ladder or a succession of bars, you can dig down "
"through any number of layers and up to five or six bricks horizontally. Just "
"return to the ladder or bars after digging each layer, then move down one "
"square, run out and dig the next layer."
msgstr ""
"Ako kopate pored merdevina ili nekoliko prečki, možete kopati duboko koliko "
"hoćete i široko pet do 6 cigli. Jednostavno kad završite svaki sloj vratite "
"merdevine ili preču."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1709
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a digging puzzle looks impossible, consider that there might be some "
"false bricks in it. Maybe the bottom layer is false or maybe you can stand "
"in a false brick and dig next to it."
msgstr ""
"Ako mozgalica kopanjem izgleda nerješiva, razmislite da možda nema lažnih "
"cigli u njoj, Možda je donji sloj lažan ili možda možete stati na lažnu "
"ciglu i kopati oko nje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1714
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Think about the order in which you will collect the gold. If you pick the "
"right order, the digging might be easier."
msgstr ""
"Razmislite kojim redosljedom kupite zlato. Ako pokupite kako treba, kopanje "
"će biti dosta lakše."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1718
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some levels require you to dig away a brick wall, run in, collect some gold "
"and run out again before the bricks close up and trap you."
msgstr ""
"Na nekim nivoima morat ćete iskopati rupu u zidu, pokupiti zlato, i vratiti "
"se prije nego se rupa zatvori."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1723
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to dig while falling through empty space, if you can get the "
"timing right. You do not need to have an enemy to ride upon. This is a bug "
"which has become a <quote>feature</quote> and is used extensively in the "
"<quote>State of Terror</quote>, <quote>Count</quote> and <quote>Curse of the "
"Mummy</quote> games."
msgstr ""
"Moguće je kopati dok propadate, ako počnete na vrijeme. Ne treba vam "
"neprijatelj da se popnete. Ovo je bag koji je postao jedna od "
"<quote>osoboina</quote> igre i koristi se u igrama <quote>Stanje Terora</"
"quote>,<quote>Broji</quote> i <quote>Kletva Mumije</quote>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1734
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Tricks with Gold</title>"
msgstr "<title>Trikovi Sa Zlatom</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1738
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot get to a piece of gold, think about getting an enemy to go "
"there and get it. Even think about using an enemy's head as a bridge to get "
"across a pit or precipice."
msgstr ""
"Ako sami ne možete pokupiti zlato, razmislite o tome da ga neprijatelj "
"pokupi za vas. Razmislite o tome da koristite glave neprijatelja kao most "
"preko rupa."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1743
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some levels there is a nugget that must be collected last of all, because "
"you will need the hidden ladders to get away from that position."
msgstr ""
"Na nekim nivoima postoji grumwn koji treba poslednji pokupiti, jer vodi do "
"skrivenih merdevina."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1748
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In some situations an enemy can be killed without giving up the gold he is "
"carrying. The gold becomes a <quote>lost nugget</quote>. You score no points "
"for making an enemy lose a nugget, but at least you can finish the level."
msgstr ""
"Ponekad, neprijatelj se može ubiti prije nego ispusti zlato koje nosu. Tada "
"zlato postaje  <quote>izgubljeni grumen</quote>. Nećete dobiti nikakve poene,"
"ali bar možete završiti nivo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1754
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there is nowhere to dig, keep the enemies running over concrete and the "
"tops of ladders and so make them release their gold at random."
msgstr ""
"Ako nemate gdje kopati, natjerajte neprijatelje da trče preko betona ili na "
"vrh merdevina tako da mogu ispustiti zlato."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1763
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Solving Difficult Levels</title>"
msgstr "<title>Rješavanje Teških Nivoa</title>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1767
#, no-c-format
msgid "Try changing the speed settings to Beginner or even lower."
msgstr ""
"Pokušajte promijeniti brzinu igre na onu za Početnike ili možda čak i niže."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1770
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the Editor feature to <quote>peek</quote> at where the false bricks and "
"hidden ladders are."
msgstr ""
"Koristite Urednik da  <quote>virnete</quote> gdje su lažne cigle i skrivene "
"merdevine."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1774
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the Editor feature to save the level in one of your own games, then you "
"can edit it so that you do not always have to start at the beginning when "
"you die. This allows you to develop the solution in easier stages."
msgstr ""
"Koristite Urednik da spasite nivo u neku od vaših igara, tako da ne morate "
"uvijek kretati ispočetka kada izgubite život. Što vam omogućava da razvijete "
"bolju strategiju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1780
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In digging puzzles, look for false bricks you can fall into and thus have "
"one less brick to dig. Or consider using an enemy to go ahead of you, so "
"that you can stand on his head and dig."
msgstr ""
"U mozgalicama kopanja, tražite lažne cigle kroz koje možete propasti, čime "
"ćete imati maje cigli za kopanje. Ili razmislite da iskoristite neprijatelja "
"da ide ispred vas dok vi stojite na njegovoj glavi i kopate."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1785
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Look for a theme or trick in the level, such as riding down on an enemy's "
"head, trapping all the enemies in a pit, luring the enemies to a corner "
"where they will stay and not chase you, luring the enemies into pits you "
"must cross to get to some gold, getting the enemies to fetch gold for you or "
"finding spots where you can stand and make an enemy move to where you want "
"him."
msgstr ""
"Potražite temu ili trik na nivou, kao što je stajanje na neprijateljovoj "
"glavi, zarobljavanje neprijatelja, namamljivanje neprijatelja u ćošak, "
"namamljivanje neprijatelja u rupu preko koje morate preći da dođete do zlata "
"ili mjesta gdje ćete stati da bi se neprijatelj kretao kako vi želite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1793
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Use <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Show A Solution...</"
#| "guimenuitem></menuchoice> to check if there is a recorded solution to the "
#| "level. This will show you some ways to handle difficulties in the level, "
#| "but not necessarily the best ways. There are often many ways to win a "
#| "level and each time you play it there are small differences in timing, "
#| "etc. So you probably will not be able to copy the recorded solution "
#| "exactly."
msgid ""
"Use the <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Show a Solution</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item to check if there is a recorded solution "
"to the level. This will show you some ways to handle difficulties in the "
"level, but not necessarily the best ways. There are often many ways to win a "
"level and each time you play it there are small differences in timing, &etc; "
"So you probably will not be able to copy the recorded solution exactly."
msgstr ""
"Koristite <menuchoice><guimenu>Pomjeri</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Prikaži "
"Rješenje...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> da vidite ima li negdje rješenje "
"nivoa. Koje će vam pomoći da pređete nivo,ali možda ne baš na najbolji "
"način. često postoji više od jednog načina da se pređe nivo, tako da "
"vjerovatno nećete identično moći ponoviti rješen nivo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1802
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Instant Replay</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> or <menuchoice><guimenu>Move</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Replay Last Level</guimenuitem></menuchoice> to replay a level "
"to a point just before you had trouble, then interrupt the replay and try "
"some other approach."
msgstr ""
"Koristite <menuchoice><guimenu>Pomjeri</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Ponovi Odmah</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> ili <menuchoice><guimenu>Pomjeri</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Ponovi zadnji nivo</guimenuitem></menuchoice> da povite nivo do "
"mjesta gdje ste zapeli, a onda prekinite ponovljeni snimak i probajte "
"drugačiji pristup."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1834
#, no-c-format
msgid "Credits and License"
msgstr "Zahvale i Licence"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1836
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kgoldrunner; copyright 2003 Ian Wadham and Marco Krüger."
msgstr "&kgoldrunner; autorska prava 2003 Ian Wadham and Marco Krüger."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1838
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kgoldrunner; is inspired by an early computer game called <trademark>Lode "
"Runner</trademark> which was written in the USA by <trademark class="
"\"copyright\">Doug Smith</trademark> and first released in 1983 by "
"<trademark class=\"copyright\">Broderbund Software</trademark>. It appeared "
"originally on the Apple II and Commodore 64 computers, which was where the "
"Wadham family and Marco Krüger became hooked. It was a major best-seller in "
"its day and is one of the all-time great computer games."
msgstr ""
"&kgoldrunner; je inspirisan ranom kompjuterskom igrom <trademark>Lode "
"Runner</trademark> koju je napisao u SAD<trademark class=\"copyright\">Doug "
"Smith</trademark> i objavio je 1983 <trademark class=\"copyright"
"\">Broderbund Software</trademark>. Pojavila se na Apple II i Commodore 64 "
"računarima, gdje su se uključili Wadham family i Marco Krüger. U svoje "
"vrijeme je bila jedna od najbolje prodavanih a i jedna je od najboljih igara "
"svih vremena."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1846
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You can find out more about <trademark>Lode Runner</trademark> and the "
#| "various versions that have come out since 1983, on the website <ulink url="
#| "\"http://entropymine.com/jason/lr\">Jason's Lode Runner Archive</ulink> "
#| "(http://entropymine.com/jason/lr/). That site also has the story of the "
#| "game's original development, in the file <ulink url=\"http://entropymine."
#| "com/jason/lr/misc/ldhist.html\"> misc/ldhist.html</ulink>. Wikipedia also "
#| "has a very good article on <trademark>Lode Runner</trademark>, with "
#| "interesting links to other sites."
msgid ""
"You can find out more about <trademark>Lode Runner</trademark> and the "
"various versions that have come out since 1983, on the website <ulink url="
"\"https://entropymine.com/jason/lr/\">Jason's Lode Runner Archive</ulink> "
"(https://entropymine.com/jason/lr/). That site also has the story of the "
"game's original development, in the file <ulink url=\"https://entropymine."
"com/jason/lr/misc/ldhist.html\"> misc/ldhist.html</ulink>. Wikipedia also "
"has a very good article on <trademark>Lode Runner</trademark>, with "
"interesting links to other sites."
msgstr ""
"Možete saznati više o <trademark>Lode Runner</trademark> i raznim verzijama "
"koje su nastale nakon 1983, na web sajtu <ulink url=\"http://entropymine.com/"
"jason/lr\">Jason's Lode Runner Archive</ulink> (http://entropymine.com/jason/"
"lr/). Tu ćete naći priču o izvornom razvoju igre, u datoteci <ulink url="
"\"http://entropymine.com/jason/lr/misc/ldhist.html\"> misc/ldhist.html</"
"ulink>. Wikipedia takođe ima veoma dobar članak o <trademark>Lode Runner</"
"trademark>, sa interesantnim linkovima na druge sajtove."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1856
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kgoldrunner; is an attempt to preserve the spirit of the original classic "
"game on a platform that will be portable and will last more than a few "
"years. It is available as free software in source code form. Copies of the "
"original game are unobtainable now and the machines it ran on are going into "
"museums."
msgstr ""
"&kgoldrunner; je pokušaj da se sačuva duh originalne klasične igre na "
"platformi koja će biti prenosiv i trajat će više od nekoliko godina. "
"Dostupan je kao slobodni softver u obliku izvornog koda . Kopije originalnog "
"igre su sada nedobavljiv i mašina je presjekao idu u muzeje ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1862
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Marco Krüger developed &kgoldrunner; as far as v0.3, out of nostalgia for "
"the original Commodore 64 game. Ian Wadham added several features and levels "
"and created the current version. Ian's elder son Peter composed the 100 "
"levels in the <quote>Initiation</quote> game and the 20 tricky levels in "
"<quote>Vengeance of Peter W</quote>. The other levels were composed by Ian, "
"Peter, Marco Krüger and friends and Ian's other children, Simon and "
"Genevieve."
msgstr ""
"Marco Krüger razvio &kgoldrunner; što se tiče v0.3 , od nostalgije za "
"originalnom Commodore 64 igrom. Ian Wadham je dodao nekoliko funkcija i "
"nivoa i stvorio trenutnu verziju . Ianov stariji sin Peter sastavio je 100 "
"nivoa u <quote>Uvodnoj</quote> igri i 20 teških nivoa u <quote> "
"Osvetoljubivost Petra W </quote>. Drugim nivoe su sastavili Ian, Peter, "
"Marco Krüger i prijatelji i Ianova druga djeca, Simon i Genevieve ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1871
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Stuart Popejoy of New York contributed the <quote>State of Terror</quote> "
"game, in 2007, the first Championship game to use &kgoldrunner; rules and "
"one of the most difficult games ever."
msgstr ""
"Stuart Popejoy iz New Yorka doprinio je  <quote> State of Terror </quote> "
"igri , u 2007. godini , prvom prvenstvu igara koje koristi &kgoldrunner; "
"pravila i jedna od najtežih igara ikad ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1876
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Steve Mann of Waterloo in Canada contributed the <quote>Count</quote> game "
"in 2008 and the <quote>Curse of the Mummy</quote> game in 2008. Both use "
"Traditional rules and both have interesting themes running through them, as "
"well as being quite difficult."
msgstr ""
"Steve Mann of Waterloo u Kanadi doprinijeli <quote> Broj</quote> igri u "
"2008. i <quote>Proklestvo mumije</quote> igri u 2008. Oba koriste "
"tradicionalne pravila i oba imaju zanimljive teme koje prolaze kroz njih , "
"osim što je prilično teško ."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1881
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Peter Wadham composed the sound effects in 2008 and Luciano Montanaro "
#| "incorporated the sounds into the KGoldrunner program."
msgid ""
"Peter Wadham composed the sound effects in 2008 and Luciano Montanaro "
"incorporated the sounds into the &kgoldrunner; program."
msgstr ""
"Peter Wadham je komponovao zvuk 2008 a  Luciano Montanaro je inkorporiraro "
"zvuk u KGoldrunner program."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1884
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Special thanks are due to Mauricio Piacentini and Dmitry Suzdalev, who "
#| "converted &kgoldrunner; to &Qt; 4 and &kde; 4, and to the many graphics "
#| "artists who contributed to the new SVG graphics and themes in the &kde; 4 "
#| "version: especially Mauricio Piacentini for the <quote>Default</quote> "
#| "theme and the new runners, Johann Ollivier Lapeyre for the ladders and "
#| "bars, Eugene Trounev for the <quote>Geek City</quote> and <quote>Treasure "
#| "of Egypt</quote> themes and, last but not least, Luciano Montanaro for "
#| "the two <quote>Nostalgia</quote> themes, the <quote>Black on White</"
#| "quote> accessibility theme, improvements to the runners, multiple "
#| "backgrounds and several other ideas."
msgid ""
"Special thanks are due to &Mauricio.Piacentini; and Dmitry Suzdalev, who "
"converted &kgoldrunner; to &Qt; 4 and &kde; 4, and to the many graphics "
"artists who contributed to the new SVG graphics and themes in the &kde; 4 "
"version: especially &Mauricio.Piacentini; for the <quote>Default</quote> "
"theme and the new runners, Johann Ollivier Lapeyre for the ladders and bars, "
"Eugene Trounev for the <quote>Geek City</quote> and <quote>Treasure of "
"Egypt</quote> themes and, last but not least, Luciano Montanaro for the two "
"<quote>Nostalgia</quote> themes, the <quote>Black on White</quote> "
"accessibility theme, improvements to the runners, multiple backgrounds and "
"several other ideas."
msgstr ""
"Posebna zahvala za Mauricio Piacentini i Dmitry Suzdalev, koji su  prebacili "
"&kgoldrunner; na &Qt; 4 i &kde; 4, te mnogim grafičkim crtačima koji su "
"doprinjeli SVG grafici i temama u &kde; 4 verziji: posebno Mauricio "
"Piacentini za <quote>Podrazumijevanu</quote> temu i nove trkače, Johann "
"Ollivier Lapeyre za platforme i prečke, Eugene Trounev za <quote>Geek grad</"
"quote> i <quote>Blago Egipta</quote> teme i na kraju, ali ne najmanje važno, "
"Luciano Montanaro za dvije <quote>Nostalgija</quote> teme, <quote>Crno na "
"bijelom</quote> temu pristupačnosti, poboljšanja trkača, više pozadina i  "
"mnoge druge ideje."

